    "steps": [
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": ";"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; This is a demonstration of how tts_seq_viewer can work for a simple earth orbiting mission."
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; The details of this sequence don't matter much, but for context, this is a toy example"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; of a sun syncronous LEO spacecraft that does 4 different science activities, (one each for the"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; northern and southern hemisphere on each of the day and night side) and one calibration"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; per orbit. On orbit 903, it also has a ground station contact with Wallops. It also yaws"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; 180 degrees to keep its solar panels sufficiently on the sun at the equator on the day side"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; "
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; This example is only meant to be realistic enough to illustrate sequence viewing and navigation"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; with regex-driven syntax highlighting and linking."
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": ";"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; In particular, not that RUN_SEQ is meant to represent a sequenced command that calls another"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; sequence. Note that the sequence that is called is highlighted in a separate color from the"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; rest of the sequence so users will immediately see that there is something different about it"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; and will be able to discover that it is a link"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": ";"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": "; In a real sequence, one might expect metatdata to also go here."
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": ";------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------"
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
            "text": ""
        },
        {
            "type": "note",
